post_text:
It's Graduation Day, Ponganset!
The PHS Class of 2020 Graduation Ceremony will be aired as follows:

The Graduation will be televised live on Capitol Television, on June 5th @ 6 pm which can be seen on Cox Channels 15 and 61, in high definition on Cox Channel 1061, on Full Channel on Channel 15 and on Channel 34 by Verizon subscribers. It will also be live streamed on this website as follows:

http://www.rilegislature.gov/CapTV/Pages/default.aspx (choose On Demand on left and then select the High School Graduation 2020 folder)

ABC6 will also be showing the Ponaganset High School Graduation Ceremony at 7pm on some of their cable stations too. Please check the following link for details. https://www.abc6.com/high-school-graduations-from-across-ri-to-air-on-abc6-subchannel-6-3/

post_text:
PLEASE SHARE:
Help Us Celebrate Ponaganset High School‚Äôs Class of 2020 with a
Spectacular Senior Send-Off!

The towns of Foster & Glocester, Ponaganset High School Administrators, and the proud parents of our graduating Ponaganset Chieftains, invite businesses & residents to decorate the towns in Green & White for Senior Week beginning June 1st! The decorated towns will be the backdrop for a Senior Car Procession through our towns! Let‚Äôs be creative decorating homes/front doors, yards, mailboxes, and storefronts with messages of congratulations! Let's rally around these kids, show our support, and honor these amazing seniors with a Spectacular Senior Sendoff!

The Procession will leave Ponaganset Middle School June 3rd at 10 am. Rain date will be June 4th. Per State guidelines, wearing a mask, and practicing appropriate social distancing will be adhered to during the procession. See attached for the procession route!

post_text: As an XQ School, we have a pretty cool chance to help honor the Class of 2020 by submitting something about our seniors (that may be aired on Graduate Together: America Honors the High School Class of 2020, Saturday, May 16). This is a big nationally televised event created by XQ and the LeBron James Family Foundation to honor all the seniors who won't have a typical graduation ceremony this year. It'll be a big show with lots of celebs and maybe some photos or videos from PHS! Submit something about your Senior here: https://graduatetogether2020.com/families
